    "created_at": "2013-06-26T00:48:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-06-26T01:02:26Z",
    "body": "The only overhead of a thread compared to a Rust task is the context switching at arbitrary points. Inserting yield checks would be much slower than just using 1:1 threading, at least on Linux, so I don't think it makes sense to do this. You're better off with context switches than yield checks in critical loops.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
