    "updated_at": "2013-06-26T01:50:49Z",
    "body": "Somewhat off-topic: I don't think `malloc` is really a potential yield point, because with jemalloc it's lock-free for allocations under 4K and only hits kernel synchronization when it actually has to make a system call (allocations over 4K, and occasionally to increase the pool size for small ones). It's never really blocking.\n",
